definition: Ming Dynasty (1368-1644)/surname Ming/Ming (c. 2000 BC), fourth of the legendary Flame Emperors, 炎帝[Yan2 di4] descended from Shennong 神農|神农[Shen2 nong2] Farmer God
bright/opposite: dark 暗[an4]/(of meaning) clear/to understand/next/public or open/wise/generic term for a sacrifice to the gods

sentences.english: She scowls at Josh, telling him to meet her in her lab at 0800 tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 她怒視傑克，讓它明早八點在她的實驗室見她。

sentences.english: Run some more tests and see me in the morning.
sentences.chinese: 再多做幾次測試，明早來見我。

sentences.english: All the morning flights get being booked up.
sentences.chinese: 所有明早的飛飛機票都預定光了。

sentences.english: Said the boy, his mother, sleep it, you would also like to go to work tomorrow morning.
sentences.chinese: 男孩說，母親，睡了吧，明早您還要上班呢。

sentences.english: Stay here for the night, and in the morning if he wants to redeem, good; let him redeem.
sentences.chinese: 你今夜在這裏住宿，明早他若肯爲你盡親屬的本分。

sentences.english: I'll sleep on your proposal and give you my answer tomorrow morning.
sentences.chinese: 今晚我好好考慮一下你的建議，明早給你個答覆。

sentences.english: Me too. I can contact a real estate agent in the morning.
sentences.chinese: 我也是，我明早聯繫一下房屋中介。

sentences.english: Could you book a taxi to take me to the train station tomorrow morning please?
sentences.chinese: 您能幫我訂輛出租車明早上送我到火車站嗎？

sentences.english: Please get the cahier ready and put in on my desk tomorrow moring.
sentences.chinese: 請把會議紀錄整理好，明早之前放在我的桌上。

sentences.english: Tarry this night, and it shall be in the morning, that if he will perform unto thee the part of a kinsman, well;
sentences.chinese: 你今夜在這裏住宿，明早他若肯爲你盡親屬的本分。

sentences.english: Then he wrote a prescription for me to fill at the drug store the next morning.
sentences.chinese: 他又在開了藥方要我明早到藥方拿藥。

sentences.english: Well, why don't you come with me to my town tomorrow morning?
sentences.chinese: 行，明早跟我去城裏兜兜吧。

sentences.english: Can I remind you to call me at 7 o'clock tomorrow morning?
sentences.chinese: 我能提醒你一下嗎？明早七點叫醒我。

sentences.english: Could you arrange for me to see Doctor Zhang tomorrow morning?
sentences.chinese: 你好，你能安排我明早看張大夫的門診嗎？

sentences.english: Yoshiaki Miyamoto hooked just one eel on his morning stint on Lake Biwa, near Kyoto.
sentences.chinese: 京都附近琵琶湖，宮本義明早上出海釣到一條鰻魚。

sentences.english: Youd better get up early tomorrow morning, otherwise you will be late for the train.
sentences.chinese: 你明早最好早起，否則就趕不上火車了。

definition: in a moment/later/also pr. [dai1 hui3 r5] or [dai1 hui5 r5]
three days from now/day after day after tomorrow
at dawn/at first light/first thing in the morning
first thing in the morning/at daybreak
as soon as possible/at the first opportunity/the sooner the better/before it's too late
